FINALIZATION OF THE PRICE, QUANTITY, AND TIME WILL BE BASED UPON PENDING REVIEW, ANALYSIS, AND NEGOTIATIONS. TARGET DATE FOR DEFINITIZATION FOR PART 2 OF THIS MODIFICATION: ON OR BEFORE NOVEMBER 15, 2015. PART 1 INVOLVES COSTS ASSOCIATED WITH PERFORMING EXPLORATORY WORK WITH DIVERS AND A HYDRAULIC EXCAVATOR AS MAY BE REQUIRED, TO DETERMINE THE ACTUAL CONDITION OF THE COFFERBOX REMNANTS, AND TO PROVIDE MORE DEFINITIVE INFORMATION FOR ACCURATELY PRICING THE REMOVAL (PART 2). THE SUBJECT MODIFICATION WILL INCLUDE ALL NECESSARY LABOR, EQUIPMENT, AND MATERAL NECESSARY TO REMOVE THE EXISTING REMAINING PORTION OF THE FORMER COFFERBOX AT THE EXISTING RIVER WALL MONOLITHS R32 AND R33, AS SHOWN ON THE ATTACHED ANNOTATED REFERENCE DRAWINGS (WITH RED CLOUDS). THE REMOVAL OF THE EXISTING COFFERBOX SHALL INCLUDE THE COMPLETE REMOVAL OF ALL REMAINING ITEMS FROM THE APPROXIMATE TOP OF TREMIE CONCRETE LEVEL TO THE BOTTOM TIP LEVELS OF THE KING PILES, SHEET PILES, CONNECTOR PILES/PLATES AND THEIR ASSOCIATED ATTACHMENTS AND BOLTS TO OTHER FEATURESAND THE RIVER WALL. THIS WORK SHALL BE PERFORMED PRIOR TO CONSTRUCTION OF THE STONE BERM AROUND THE CLOSURES CELL/CLOSURE WEDGE CURRENTLY WITHIN THE SCOPE OF THE M22 TO M27 CONTRACT.
